Package: survalis
Type: Package
Title: Interpretable Survival Machine Learning and Explainability Tools
Version: 0.6.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = c("Imad", "El"),
           family = "Badisy",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           email = "elbadisyimad@gmail.com"))
Description: A modular toolkit for interpretable survival machine learning.
    Includes built-in learners (statistical, tree-based, gradient boosting,
    and deep learning models) and supports user-defined models that return
    time-indexed survival probability matrices. Provides model-agnostic
    interpretability methods such as SHAP, partial dependence plot (PDP), accumulated
    local effects (ALE), surrogate models, counterfactuals, interactions, feature importance, and calibration
    utilities. Designed to integrate via a unified fit/predict/tune interface.
